cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with machine learning algorithms for classification and active learning, which are typically categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of disagreement-based active learning and rejection rates also suggests a possible categorization under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of rejection rates in the context of image classification also suggests a possible categorization under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of Hanneke's disagreement coefficient and its role in the analysis of the algorithms suggests a possible categorization under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
